WEBVTT

00:09.444 --> 00:09.661
.

00:09.705 --> 00:11.402
- In the criminal justice
system,

00:11.446 --> 00:12.708
sexually based offenses

00:12.751 --> 00:15.189
are considered
especially heinous.

00:15.232 --> 00:17.582
In New York City,
the dedicated detectives

00:17.626 --> 00:19.323
who investigate
these vicious felonies

00:19.367 --> 00:20.803
are members of an elite squad

00:20.846 --> 00:22.848
known as
the Special Victims Unit.

00:22.892 --> 00:24.459
These are their stories.

00:26.722 --> 00:29.464
- Come on, you guys wanna be
lifeguards or what?

00:29.507 --> 00:31.553
Almost there. Finish strong.

00:33.163 --> 00:34.686
That's what I'm talking about.
Let's go!

00:34.730 --> 00:36.210
Come on, Worsley,
don't gas out now, man!

00:36.253 --> 00:38.168
You're so close!
Every second counts!

00:39.735 --> 00:42.216
- That's what
I'm talking about.

00:42.259 --> 00:44.783
Here. Cover yourself up.
- Oh, thanks.

00:44.827 --> 00:46.394
- Nice swimsuit.
- Thanks.

00:46.437 --> 00:48.178
- What's your name?
- Martina Rodriguez.

00:48.222 --> 00:50.093
- Martina, nice to meet you.

00:50.137 --> 00:51.660
Now wait--

00:51.703 --> 00:54.184
don't tell me you're
this guy's little sister.

00:54.228 --> 00:56.056
- I met you last year
when I came to pick

00:56.099 --> 00:57.057
Diego up from the beach.

00:57.100 --> 00:58.928
- Oh. Yeah, right.

00:58.971 --> 01:00.190
Damn, son.

01:00.234 --> 01:01.887
Been hitting the gym
since last year, huh?

01:01.931 --> 01:03.324
- Started doing jujitsu.

01:05.239 --> 01:07.110
- Well, I haven't seen
your sister's times,

01:07.154 --> 01:09.460
but she looks like
a real fish in that pool.

01:09.504 --> 01:11.462
- All right, people, listen up.

01:11.506 --> 01:14.291
Chief's gonna handle
the CPR portion of the exam.

01:14.335 --> 01:16.380
- Hey, Rodney, have you
seen that prop dummy?

01:16.424 --> 01:17.642
- It wasn't in the
storage closet?

01:17.686 --> 01:18.774
- No.

01:18.817 --> 01:20.210
- Those Water Rescue guys
from Queens

01:20.254 --> 01:22.430
must have packed it
in the van by accident.

01:22.473 --> 01:24.388
- All right,
I'm gonna need a volunteer.

01:24.432 --> 01:26.086
Uh, what's your name again?
- Martina.

01:26.129 --> 01:27.522
- Martina, right.

01:27.565 --> 01:30.612
Hey, can you--
you lay down right here?

01:30.655 --> 01:31.656
- Thanks.

01:31.700 --> 01:32.962
- Here you go.

01:33.005 --> 01:34.398
- Like this?
- Perfect.

01:34.442 --> 01:36.879
- Okay.
- Just lay back. Good.

01:36.922 --> 01:38.402
All right, guys, today,

01:38.446 --> 01:40.404
we're gonna be graded
on our ABCs:

01:40.448 --> 01:43.146
Airway, Breathing, Circulation,

01:43.190 --> 01:44.365
which means
I'm gonna be looking

01:44.408 --> 01:47.411
for the proper head tilt,
rescue breaths,

01:47.455 --> 01:50.110
and the timing
of your compressions.

01:50.153 --> 01:51.459
Got it?

01:54.288 --> 01:56.072
- Hey, Rodney, can you ask
Rodriguez's sister

01:56.116 --> 01:57.073
to come in for a second,
please?

01:57.117 --> 01:58.074
- Yeah, sure.

01:58.118 --> 01:59.206
- Thank you.

02:06.387 --> 02:07.562
- You wanted to see me?

02:07.605 --> 02:08.911
- Yeah, Martina.

02:08.954 --> 02:09.868
Come on in.

02:12.262 --> 02:13.350
Close the door.

02:19.139 --> 02:20.444
- So what's up?

02:20.488 --> 02:22.185
- Well, technically,
you did great with your CPR,

02:22.229 --> 02:23.447
but it's your times.

02:23.491 --> 02:24.666
You're on the bubble.

02:24.709 --> 02:26.798
- What? I didn't qualify?
- Relax.

02:26.842 --> 02:29.105
I'm gonna give you a chance
to do it again next week.

02:29.149 --> 02:33.065
But listen, it--it's not about
how often you practice but how.

02:33.109 --> 02:35.242
And if you don't mind my
asking, who's training you?

02:35.285 --> 02:37.157
- My brother.

02:37.200 --> 02:38.288
- That's the problem.

02:38.332 --> 02:39.811
Kid's too easy on you.

02:39.855 --> 02:40.899
Come here.

02:40.943 --> 02:42.814
Let me show you something.

02:42.858 --> 02:43.815
Give me this.

02:43.859 --> 02:44.860
All right.

02:44.903 --> 02:46.209
Put your arms up,
all the way up.

02:46.253 --> 02:48.429
There we go.
Imagine you're in the water.

02:48.472 --> 02:49.778
Speaking of the water,
you're too flat in the water.

02:49.821 --> 02:51.780
You got to move your
hips, all right?

02:51.823 --> 02:53.738
There we go. There we go.

02:53.782 --> 02:56.132
That's the one move.
That works.

02:56.176 --> 02:57.742
And move, and move.
There you go.

02:57.786 --> 02:59.266
You feel the difference?
- Mm.

02:59.309 --> 03:00.484
- Yeah. Feel the water.

03:00.528 --> 03:02.573
All right. That's it.

03:02.617 --> 03:05.750
[suspenseful music]

03:05.794 --> 03:10.233
♪

03:10.277 --> 03:11.930
- Martina, hey.

03:11.974 --> 03:13.367
What were you doing in there?

03:13.410 --> 03:15.325
- Greco just wanted
to go over my scores.

03:17.632 --> 03:19.938
- Hey, yo, Chief.
- Hey. What'd I do?

03:19.982 --> 03:22.550
- Diego! Diego!

03:22.593 --> 03:24.116
- Yo, yo, chill! D, get off.
D, get off.

03:24.160 --> 03:25.248
- Get away from me!
- That's enough!

03:25.292 --> 03:26.684
- I mean it!
- That's enough, bro.

03:26.728 --> 03:28.686
- If I ever see you here
again, I'll kill you, bro.

03:28.730 --> 03:31.559
- Stop! Stop!
- I swear to God.

03:31.602 --> 03:32.386
Let's go.

03:32.429 --> 03:33.691
- What is wrong with you?

03:33.735 --> 03:40.655
♪

03:47.401 --> 03:49.446
Dude, what's your problem?

03:49.490 --> 03:51.274
- What were you doing
in his office?

03:51.318 --> 03:52.797
- I told you.

03:52.841 --> 03:54.843
Said he'd help me pass,
but not after what you pulled.

03:56.975 --> 03:59.848
- Diego, what'd I say about
drinking under my roof, huh?

03:59.891 --> 04:01.371
- Whatever, Ma.
I'm out of here then.

04:01.415 --> 04:02.807
- Qué?
- [speaking Spanish]

04:02.851 --> 04:04.418
- Mira!

04:04.461 --> 04:05.723
You better not
walk out that door.

04:05.767 --> 04:07.377
- [speaking Spanish]
- You better not leave.

04:07.421 --> 04:09.423
No. You better not leave.

04:15.080 --> 04:17.126
- You got plans for tonight?

04:17.169 --> 04:19.476
- Yeah,
gonna put the girls down,

04:19.520 --> 04:21.304
eat my feelings on the couch,

04:21.348 --> 04:23.306
wait for Carisi to come over.

04:23.350 --> 04:25.003
- You two don't
live together yet?

04:25.047 --> 04:26.614
- He has a drawer.

04:28.355 --> 04:30.922
- It's a waste of gas,
if you ask me.

04:30.966 --> 04:33.316
And by the way,
I got something for you.

04:33.360 --> 04:34.448
- Hmm?

04:47.287 --> 04:48.723
A bullet?

04:48.766 --> 04:52.640
- Same caliber as the one
you got shot with.

04:52.683 --> 04:55.512
You have to own your trauma,
or your trauma will own you.

04:57.949 --> 04:59.168
- Hey, guys.

04:59.211 --> 05:00.778
Just got a call from the 1-1,

05:00.822 --> 05:02.171
asking for somebody
to go down there.

05:02.214 --> 05:03.346
You guys take it?

05:05.305 --> 05:07.219
Thanks.

05:07.263 --> 05:09.352
- Why don't you go home?

05:09.396 --> 05:10.919
- No.

05:10.962 --> 05:12.355
I got this.

05:12.399 --> 05:15.837
But, um, I'm driving.

05:20.842 --> 05:24.062
- Diego Rodriguez, 19, picked
him up in a bar in Midtown,

05:24.106 --> 05:27.239
drunk, picking fights,
talking about some guy

05:27.283 --> 05:28.415
who had a run-in
with his sister.

05:28.458 --> 05:29.459
- What kind of run-in?

05:29.503 --> 05:30.634
- How the hell would I know?

05:30.678 --> 05:32.506
Sergeant had me call you guys.

05:32.549 --> 05:35.291
- Heard that before.
- Hmm.

05:35.335 --> 05:36.597
Hey, there.
I'm Detective Rollins.

05:36.640 --> 05:39.382
This is Sergeant Tutuola.

05:39.426 --> 05:40.731
- So what's going on, man?

05:40.775 --> 05:43.560
What happened with your sister?

05:43.604 --> 05:47.564
- You know, when my--
my pops was dying,

05:47.608 --> 05:50.045
he said to look out for her.

05:50.088 --> 05:51.655
And I was just trying
to protect her.

05:51.699 --> 05:53.483
- Protect her from what?

05:53.527 --> 05:55.355
- From Paul Greco.

05:55.398 --> 05:57.487
He's the head
of the lifeguards.

05:57.531 --> 05:59.402
[suspenseful music]

05:59.446 --> 06:01.056
- So what,
he raped your sister?

06:03.363 --> 06:05.539
- No.

06:05.582 --> 06:06.540
He raped me.

06:06.583 --> 06:13.721
♪

06:15.070 --> 06:18.029
[dramatic music]

06:18.073 --> 06:24.993
♪

07:05.468 --> 07:06.469
- Am I under arrest?

07:06.513 --> 07:07.862
- Your arrest was voided.

07:07.905 --> 07:09.385
- Good,
because I want to go home.

07:09.429 --> 07:10.865
I didn't have
dinner last night.

07:10.908 --> 07:12.997
- You're free to leave,
but I got you a sandwich,

07:13.041 --> 07:14.434
something to drink.

07:14.477 --> 07:16.392
Have this first.

07:16.436 --> 07:18.481
- We wanted to talk to you.

07:18.525 --> 07:20.744
Diego, do you remember
telling us last night

07:20.788 --> 07:24.052
that your boss
sexually assaulted you?

07:24.095 --> 07:25.357
- No, no, no, no, no.

07:25.401 --> 07:27.142
I was just wasted
last night, man.

07:27.185 --> 07:29.449
Greco's going after
my sister, Martina, okay?

07:29.492 --> 07:31.363
- Martina's a lifeguard too?

07:31.407 --> 07:33.191
- She wants to be.

07:33.235 --> 07:35.498
Greco has the power
to make it happen or not.

07:35.542 --> 07:36.717
- Okay, yeah.

07:36.760 --> 07:38.545
Can you tell us more
about that?

07:40.024 --> 07:41.025
- At the pool yesterday,

07:41.069 --> 07:43.375
we both took
the qualifying test.

07:43.419 --> 07:46.944
Later, I saw her coming out
of Greco's office upset,

07:46.988 --> 07:48.250
and I snapped.

07:48.293 --> 07:51.166
- And what did she say
happened in that office?

07:51.209 --> 07:53.255
- Nothing. She's innocent.

07:53.298 --> 07:54.909
Martina doesn't see Greco
for what he really is.

07:54.952 --> 07:56.388
- And you do.
- Of course.

07:56.432 --> 07:57.781
- Where's my brother?
- What do you think Greco is?

07:57.825 --> 07:59.261
Do you know that girl?

07:59.304 --> 08:00.610
- Diego!
- Martina!

08:00.654 --> 08:01.829
- Are you okay?
- What are you doing here?

08:01.872 --> 08:03.134
- Hey, hey.
- I told her not to come.

08:03.178 --> 08:04.484
She don't listen, apparently.
- You know what?

08:04.527 --> 08:05.746
- Are you okay?
- Martina, what are you doing?

08:05.789 --> 08:07.095
I told you not to come.

08:07.138 --> 08:08.575
- I'm gonna go talk to her.
Everything's okay.

08:08.618 --> 08:10.185
Come with me.
Come with me this way.

08:10.228 --> 08:12.535
- Look, man.
- She don't listen. I'm sorry.

08:12.579 --> 08:14.145
- Your sister's got your back.

08:14.189 --> 08:16.147
- Can you just tell her that
I'm all right, that I'm okay,

08:16.191 --> 08:18.062
everything's good?

08:18.106 --> 08:20.108
- Look, man.

08:20.151 --> 08:23.764
I know how hard it is to talk
about this, but what happened?

08:23.807 --> 08:25.330
- Nothing happened.

08:25.374 --> 08:26.984
You don't understand that,
or what?

08:29.204 --> 08:31.772
- Even if something did,

08:31.815 --> 08:33.861
doesn't make you
any less of a man.

08:36.254 --> 08:38.996
[solemn music]

08:39.040 --> 08:41.259
- I heard lifeguards make bank.

08:41.303 --> 08:44.306
I needed money for college,
so I test.

08:44.349 --> 08:45.612
- With Greco?

08:45.655 --> 08:48.266
- Yeah, with Greco, last year.

08:48.310 --> 08:51.835
He called me into his office
after, said I didn't qualify,

08:51.879 --> 08:54.795
that I picked up some bad
habits on the school team.

08:54.838 --> 08:57.449
I could pass if I let him
retrain me.

08:57.493 --> 08:59.190
- It was craziness yesterday.

09:00.801 --> 09:02.150
I came out of Greco's office,

09:02.193 --> 09:05.283
eyes leaking because
I didn't qualify, and...

09:07.285 --> 09:09.418
Diego saw the tears.

09:09.461 --> 09:11.028
He flew into a roid rage.

09:12.595 --> 09:14.162
Why?

09:14.205 --> 09:15.859
Did Greco press charges?

09:15.903 --> 09:17.513
- No.

09:17.557 --> 09:19.036
- Then why is my brother here?

09:21.212 --> 09:25.695
- One day,
Greco says the only reason

09:25.739 --> 09:29.830
he hooked me up with the job
was 'cause of my...

09:35.183 --> 09:38.273
This was before I started
learning how to fight.

09:38.316 --> 09:39.796
- It's okay, man.

09:42.756 --> 09:46.673
- He forced me down
on his desk, face down.

09:48.370 --> 09:49.806
And he--

09:52.461 --> 09:53.767
He did it to me.

09:56.813 --> 09:58.336
After that, I cleaned up.

09:59.947 --> 10:02.210
From that point forward,
I got all the posts

10:02.253 --> 10:03.864
and all the OT I wanted.

10:05.213 --> 10:08.216
And he never tried
nothing again.

10:08.259 --> 10:09.391
- You ever tell anyone?

10:09.434 --> 10:14.744
♪

10:14.788 --> 10:17.312
And when your sister
wanted to be a lifeguard,

10:17.355 --> 10:19.140
you never warned her?

10:19.183 --> 10:20.532
- Nah, man.

10:20.576 --> 10:21.751
I didn't even realize it.

10:21.795 --> 10:23.231
I just thought
he was into guys.

10:27.801 --> 10:29.629
- So talk to me about
this Chief Greco.

10:29.672 --> 10:31.108
- He works for the
lifeguard division

10:31.152 --> 10:34.111
of Parks and Recreation,
Bronx County, administrator.

10:34.155 --> 10:36.592
- He oversees all the
public pools in the Bronx,

10:36.636 --> 10:37.941
some of the beaches.

10:37.985 --> 10:39.247
He's been there for ten years.

10:39.290 --> 10:40.422
- Okay, any priors?

10:40.465 --> 10:41.902
- Not in the system.

10:41.945 --> 10:43.686
- The job pays double
the average salary

10:43.730 --> 10:45.819
for teens and 20-somethings,
plenty of OT.

10:45.862 --> 10:47.777
- You get paid a lot
to sit on a beach.

10:47.821 --> 10:49.083
- Sign me up.

10:49.126 --> 10:50.432
- We called around
the Parks Department.

10:50.475 --> 10:52.695
They all say Greco's friendly,
smart, single,

10:52.739 --> 10:54.392
got a bit of a rep
as a player but nothing

10:54.436 --> 10:55.698
like what Diego's saying.

10:55.742 --> 10:56.699
- All right, so what do we know
about Diego

10:56.743 --> 10:58.092
and the sister Martina?

10:58.135 --> 11:01.051
- Good kids from the projects,
straight A's.

11:01.095 --> 11:03.053
Diego had a massive
stress reaction

11:03.097 --> 11:04.620
when he told me what happened.

11:04.664 --> 11:06.448
He's got no reason
to lie to me.

11:06.491 --> 11:08.668
- Well, that's not good.

11:08.711 --> 11:11.758
But no outcry at the time
and no rape kit.

11:11.801 --> 11:13.368
- You want us to keep digging?

11:13.411 --> 11:15.196
- It's a bit of a risk, right,

11:15.239 --> 11:17.285
having Greco find out
that we're onto him?

11:17.328 --> 11:18.590
- Yeah.

11:18.634 --> 11:20.680
So we'll go straight to him,
see if he blinks.

11:24.814 --> 11:27.338
- Diego said that
I sexually assaulted him?

11:27.382 --> 11:28.731
- He did.

11:28.775 --> 11:30.733
We're here to get
your side of the story.

11:32.779 --> 11:34.041
- [exhales]

11:35.695 --> 11:39.307
- So, did you?

11:39.350 --> 11:41.657
- Of course not. No.

11:41.701 --> 11:43.224
Diego was upset yesterday

11:43.267 --> 11:45.356
because I was talking
with his sister.

11:45.400 --> 11:46.967
- It's retaliation?

11:47.010 --> 11:51.493
- Why didn't you report
the physical assault?

11:51.536 --> 11:53.364
- Because I like the kid.

11:53.408 --> 11:56.628
He was so sweet last year.
Then this year, he comes in.

11:56.672 --> 11:57.934
He's all jacked up.

11:57.978 --> 11:59.893
He wants to start a fight.

11:59.936 --> 12:01.808
I don't know.

12:01.851 --> 12:03.157
It's none of my business.

12:03.200 --> 12:05.333
But honestly,
I wouldn't be surprised

12:05.376 --> 12:07.814
if the kid's on some kind
of steroids or something.

12:07.857 --> 12:10.338
- Those muscles are armor.

12:10.381 --> 12:11.513
- Armor for what?

12:11.556 --> 12:13.297
- You tell me.

12:13.341 --> 12:16.605
[tense music]

12:16.648 --> 12:20.783
- So what exactly happened
between you and Martina

12:20.827 --> 12:23.003
in your office?

12:23.046 --> 12:24.395
- She didn't qualify.

12:24.439 --> 12:27.311
I told her. She cried.

12:27.355 --> 12:28.791
I felt bad.

12:28.835 --> 12:30.097
These are--
these are hardworking kids

12:30.140 --> 12:32.926
from a really poor family.

12:32.969 --> 12:37.582
She got so close,
so I offered to train her.

12:37.626 --> 12:38.888
You can ask my

12:38.932 --> 12:40.107
second-in-command,
Ronnie Volpe.

12:40.150 --> 12:42.718
He's at Jonas Bronck Beach
today--

12:42.762 --> 12:44.241
with Diego.

12:44.285 --> 12:46.461
- So you're telling me
Diego went to work?

12:46.504 --> 12:51.031
- I care about the kid,
and I'm short-staffed.

12:51.074 --> 12:52.336
Diego was a little late today.

12:52.380 --> 12:55.949
So now I understand why.

12:57.864 --> 13:00.867
I'm sorry.
None of this makes any sense.

13:00.910 --> 13:04.218
If I assaulted the kid, why--
why would he come to work?

13:04.261 --> 13:07.830
- So you never had any
sexual contact with Diego?

13:07.874 --> 13:08.831
- No.

13:08.875 --> 13:15.969
♪

13:17.013 --> 13:19.407
- I had to pull Diego
off Greco.

13:19.450 --> 13:20.625
Look, I don't know
what happened

13:20.669 --> 13:22.410
between last year and now,

13:22.453 --> 13:24.586
but the kid's like
a totally different person.

13:24.629 --> 13:26.675
- You sure nothing happened
to his little sister?

13:26.718 --> 13:28.024
- Oh, I'm sure.
- All right.

13:28.068 --> 13:29.373
So when he showed up
for work this morning,

13:29.417 --> 13:31.332
what was that like?
Were you surprised at all?

13:31.375 --> 13:34.074
- After he tried to kick
the chief's ass, yeah.

13:34.117 --> 13:36.250
But to be honest,
I was more taken aback

13:36.293 --> 13:38.861
by how he looked
when he clocked in.

13:38.905 --> 13:40.732
I could smell the booze.

13:40.776 --> 13:41.821
- Where is he now?

13:43.126 --> 13:45.737
- Out swimming laps
between the buoys.

13:45.781 --> 13:47.348
Pinsky's rules.

13:47.391 --> 13:48.740
Any time one of
these kids shows up

13:48.784 --> 13:50.699
after a late night of partying.

13:50.742 --> 13:53.310
Quick way to sober up.

13:53.354 --> 13:54.355
- Thank you.

13:58.141 --> 13:59.534
Say what you want
about Fin and Benson.

13:59.577 --> 14:01.797
At least they don't
make us swim laps.

14:01.841 --> 14:03.712
- What do you think this
little trip to the beach is?

14:03.755 --> 14:05.801
- What, you think kid's lying?

14:05.845 --> 14:07.237
- I mean, you hear Volpe.

14:07.281 --> 14:08.891
The kid came to work
like nothing happened.

14:08.935 --> 14:11.154
- Maybe Diego figures
if he acts normal,

14:11.198 --> 14:13.156
everything might
actually be normal.

14:13.200 --> 14:15.289
- Would you go out partying
in--in the same day

14:15.332 --> 14:16.986
you accused somebody of rape?

14:17.030 --> 14:19.467
- No, but I'd sure
as hell be drinking.

14:22.383 --> 14:24.211
- You Pinsky?

14:24.254 --> 14:26.256
- Yeah. Who wants to know?

14:26.300 --> 14:27.779
- NYPD.

14:27.823 --> 14:28.868
- What can I do for you?

14:28.911 --> 14:30.521
- Pretty far out there, no?

14:30.565 --> 14:32.349
- Yeah, he'll be all right.

14:33.655 --> 14:35.178
- You sure?

14:35.222 --> 14:37.267
[suspenseful music]

14:37.311 --> 14:39.095
Sure looks like
he's in trouble.

14:40.967 --> 14:42.490
[whistle trills]

14:42.533 --> 14:44.144
- Diego!

14:44.187 --> 14:46.276
[whistle trills]
Diego!

14:48.888 --> 14:50.802
Diego!

14:50.846 --> 14:51.978
- Yo, you gonna go in?

14:52.021 --> 14:53.936
- Give it a minute.

14:53.980 --> 14:55.416
- What are you doing?

14:55.459 --> 14:56.939
What are you doing?
Hey, Velasco!

14:58.854 --> 15:01.944
[whistle trilling]

15:01.988 --> 15:08.559
♪

15:09.734 --> 15:11.693
[whistle trills]
- Diego!

15:11.736 --> 15:13.913
♪

15:18.569 --> 15:18.787
.

15:18.830 --> 15:21.007
- They're gonna take
him to Montefiore.

15:21.050 --> 15:22.573
- Maybe he's got a chance.

15:22.617 --> 15:26.447
- Velasco, they just did CPR
on him for 30 minutes.

15:26.490 --> 15:27.535
- We just watched a kid drown.

15:27.578 --> 15:29.102
- No, you didn't.

15:29.145 --> 15:30.755
That lazy scumbag did.

15:30.799 --> 15:33.584
- Hey, look, I understand
I had a duty to act.

15:33.628 --> 15:35.195
But I stepped in,
I observed that

15:35.238 --> 15:36.326
the conditions had changed

15:36.370 --> 15:38.502
and there was now
a rip current.

15:38.546 --> 15:40.461
I feared
for my life and safety.

15:43.855 --> 15:45.118
- Captain.

15:45.161 --> 15:47.337
Trauma docs just called it.

15:49.470 --> 15:51.124
- Oh, Fin.

15:51.167 --> 15:52.299
I'm so sorry.

15:52.342 --> 15:53.691
- Me?

15:53.735 --> 15:54.997
Velasco.

15:55.041 --> 15:57.695
Muncy said Diego
was limp in his arms

15:57.739 --> 15:59.654
when he pulled him
out of the water.

15:59.697 --> 16:02.483
- Are you thinking
what I'm thinking?

16:02.526 --> 16:04.224
- That Diego was
sent into the water

16:04.267 --> 16:06.487
to teach him some other lesson
that had nothing to do

16:06.530 --> 16:07.879
with the hangover?
- Yeah.

16:07.923 --> 16:10.621
- After we told Greco about
Diego's allegations?

16:10.665 --> 16:12.754
Yeah, that thought
crossed my mind.

16:12.797 --> 16:14.669
- Means the allegations
are true.

16:14.712 --> 16:16.410
- We can't prove it.

16:16.453 --> 16:17.759
Our only witness is dead.

16:17.802 --> 16:19.326
Even Carisi couldn't
make that stick.

16:19.369 --> 16:21.806
- A predator like Greco just
doesn't pop out of nowhere.

16:21.850 --> 16:24.461
He's had that position
for ten years.

16:25.680 --> 16:27.551
- Find his other victims.

16:33.079 --> 16:37.735
- Diego loved the water,
even as a young boy.

16:37.779 --> 16:44.177
All the swimming he did,
it healed his heart

16:44.220 --> 16:47.528
after losing his father.

16:47.571 --> 16:50.705
In the Bible, it says,

16:50.748 --> 16:53.055
"When you pass
through the waters,

16:53.099 --> 16:54.665
God is with you."

16:54.709 --> 16:57.494
And now they're together
at peace.

16:57.538 --> 16:59.714
- We're so sorry for your loss.

17:01.063 --> 17:02.499
- Mami, why don't you
go lay down?

17:02.543 --> 17:04.240
- Okay.

17:04.284 --> 17:05.807
Thank you.

17:15.077 --> 17:17.123
- I drove Diego
to work this morning.

17:17.166 --> 17:19.299
He told me what Greco
did to him last year,

17:19.342 --> 17:21.518
but he made me promise our
mother would never find out.

17:21.562 --> 17:23.390
- We understand.

17:23.433 --> 17:24.652
She doesn't need
to know about it,

17:24.695 --> 17:26.654
at least not right now.

17:26.697 --> 17:28.525
- You're gonna arrest Greco
for raping my brother.

17:28.569 --> 17:31.746
- That's what we're trying
to do, Martina.

17:31.789 --> 17:34.444
- Greco suggested
he mentored you.

17:34.488 --> 17:37.143
That's called grooming.

17:37.186 --> 17:39.406
With all the other candidates,
he had to make

17:39.449 --> 17:42.061
that same offer to someone.

17:42.104 --> 17:43.671
- Maybe last year?

17:43.714 --> 17:45.803
- I might know someone.

17:51.418 --> 17:53.115
- Please come in.

17:53.159 --> 17:55.813
I heard Diego drowned.

17:55.857 --> 17:57.728
- How'd you two meet?

17:57.772 --> 17:59.817
- From the neighborhood.

17:59.861 --> 18:01.689
He was my first love.

18:01.732 --> 18:04.561
I was his too.

18:04.605 --> 18:07.129
Guess now his last.

18:07.173 --> 18:10.045
- Daniela, we're investigating
something Diego told us,

18:10.089 --> 18:12.700
and we think that happened
while you two were together.

18:12.743 --> 18:14.702
- Is this about Paul Greco?

18:18.053 --> 18:20.316
- Diego mentioned that he
was inappropriate with him?

18:20.360 --> 18:22.884
- What? No.

18:22.927 --> 18:24.799
They were really close.

18:24.842 --> 18:27.236
Diego viewed him
as a father figure.

18:27.280 --> 18:30.370
- Just curious, why--
why would you think that

18:30.413 --> 18:31.936
we were here to talk
about Greco?

18:34.330 --> 18:36.202
- Because Greco raped me.

18:37.986 --> 18:41.468
I never told Diego, but I
suspected he might have known.

18:41.511 --> 18:44.166
That's why I broke up with him.

18:44.210 --> 18:46.386
I needed to be held.

18:46.429 --> 18:48.823
Diego didn't even
want to touch me.

18:48.866 --> 18:52.000
I thought he was
just loyal to Greco.

18:52.043 --> 18:55.003
- Daniela, I hate
to say this, but...

18:55.046 --> 18:57.440
it's likely Diego
didn't want to be touched

18:57.484 --> 18:59.747
because the same thing
happened to him.

18:59.790 --> 19:02.010
[suspenseful music]

19:02.053 --> 19:05.405
- I thought Greco
was just into girls.

19:05.448 --> 19:08.016
I mean, there was always rumors
about him being a dog.

19:08.059 --> 19:10.627
On the beach,
I'd hear them at parties.

19:10.671 --> 19:12.151
Diego pulled some strings
and got me

19:12.194 --> 19:13.674
an interview with Greco
halfway through summer

19:13.717 --> 19:15.589
when I got laid off.

19:17.678 --> 19:19.462
Greco said it was offseason,

19:19.506 --> 19:21.247
so he'd have
to qualify me privately.

19:22.987 --> 19:26.774
He took me into his office
and pinned me down.

19:29.255 --> 19:31.561
I had no business being
a lifeguard anyway.

19:32.693 --> 19:33.824
- Why is that?

19:35.261 --> 19:38.089
- Because I can barely swim.

19:40.266 --> 19:43.834
- Did you tell anyone about
what Greco did to you?

19:43.878 --> 19:46.663
- I reported it to the precinct
here in the Bronx.

19:46.707 --> 19:49.231
- Did you do a rape kit?

19:49.275 --> 19:52.365
- Yeah, but they
never called me back.

19:52.408 --> 19:59.328
♪

20:01.417 --> 20:02.723
- Pool's closed.

20:02.766 --> 20:04.551
- Paul Greco,
you're under arrest

20:04.594 --> 20:06.640
for the rape of Daniela Cruz.

20:06.683 --> 20:08.511
- I have no idea who that is.

20:08.555 --> 20:10.252
- She knows you.

20:15.475 --> 20:15.692
.

20:15.736 --> 20:18.565
- Paul Greco, on the charge
of rape in the first degree,

20:18.608 --> 20:19.653
how do you plead?

20:19.696 --> 20:21.176
- Not guilty, Your Honor.

20:21.220 --> 20:23.439
- People on bail?
- We request $75,000.

20:23.483 --> 20:25.180
The defendant is
facing serious charges,

20:25.224 --> 20:26.747
and he has the resources
to flee.

20:26.790 --> 20:28.705
- Chief Greco is a
well-regarded civil servant,

20:28.749 --> 20:31.578
no record, who only wants
to defend his reputation.

20:31.621 --> 20:33.101
We request ROR.

20:33.144 --> 20:36.757
- Sorry, Counselor Carisi,
I'm granting ROR.

20:36.800 --> 20:39.020
Bailiff, next case.

20:39.063 --> 20:42.328
- Docket number 1625A366.
Please approach.

20:42.371 --> 20:43.633
- Braun's being a prick.

20:43.677 --> 20:45.069
He flat-out refused
to even discuss a deal.

20:45.113 --> 20:46.680
- The eighth floor really wants
to plead this out?

20:46.723 --> 20:47.942
- And the mayor's office.

20:47.985 --> 20:50.161
Nobody wants a long-term
city chief on trial.

20:50.205 --> 20:51.511
It shows incompetency
on their part.

20:51.554 --> 20:53.034
It makes them look bad,
dirty laundry.

20:53.077 --> 20:54.514
- Oh, please.

20:54.557 --> 20:56.603
McGrath's been chewing the end
of my phone for days.

20:56.646 --> 20:58.866
- Counselor, Captain,
can I have a moment?

20:58.909 --> 21:00.824
Assemblywoman Diane Garcia.

21:00.868 --> 21:02.173
- How can we help you?

21:02.217 --> 21:04.698
- I just wanted to put
in a word for Paul Greco.

21:04.741 --> 21:06.134
He's a decent man.

21:06.177 --> 21:07.962
- Well, we have evidence
of rape one, Miss Garcia.

21:08.005 --> 21:09.180
We're going to the grand jury.

21:09.224 --> 21:11.052
- I'm just asking
that you think about it

21:11.095 --> 21:13.794
before you ruin a respected
city official's reputation

21:13.837 --> 21:17.841
and put the city in danger
of civil litigation.

21:17.885 --> 21:19.365
- Thank you for the heads up.

21:22.237 --> 21:23.717
- You just made a friend.

21:23.760 --> 21:26.023
- Well, she just oversees
judicial appointments,

21:26.067 --> 21:29.375
bail reform, court procedure,
and district attorney budget.

21:29.418 --> 21:30.593
So yeah,
nothing to worry about.

21:30.637 --> 21:32.465
- How much you want
to bet Greco's

21:32.508 --> 21:34.597
a campaign contributor?

21:34.641 --> 21:36.295
Ah, good news.

21:36.338 --> 21:39.559
Daniela's rape kit came back.

21:39.602 --> 21:40.647
DNA's a match.

21:40.690 --> 21:41.822
- The Bronx actually
came through?

21:41.865 --> 21:43.258
- Well, kicking, screaming.

21:43.302 --> 21:44.433
- Well, the Bronx doesn't do
anything by the book.

21:44.477 --> 21:46.435
- Yeah, especially their SVU.

21:50.961 --> 21:52.049
- Daniela's still not here?

21:52.093 --> 21:53.355
- No, she's not.

21:53.399 --> 21:54.574
The grand jury convenes
in five minutes.

21:54.617 --> 21:56.097
I thought you prepped her.
- I did.

21:56.140 --> 21:57.664
She knows when and where.
Let me give her another call.

21:57.707 --> 21:59.143
- Yeah.

22:00.754 --> 22:02.538
- Daniela,
it's Detective Rollins.

22:02.582 --> 22:04.018
We're at the court,
waiting for you.

22:04.061 --> 22:05.367
Please give me a call back.

22:05.411 --> 22:06.499
- Don't tell me
that we're getting

22:06.542 --> 22:08.414
ghosted by our star witness--

22:08.457 --> 22:10.938
by our only witness.

22:10.981 --> 22:12.461
- I'll send Muncy and Velasco.

22:12.505 --> 22:14.594
[suspenseful music]

22:14.637 --> 22:17.205
- I'm sorry I didn't
tell anyone, but I can't do it.

22:17.248 --> 22:18.293
I can't testify.

22:18.337 --> 22:19.773
- What's going on, Daniela?

22:21.427 --> 22:23.429
- My father's on parole.

22:23.472 --> 22:24.865
Greco must have gotten
to his officer

22:24.908 --> 22:27.215
because he threatened
to have my father violated.

22:27.258 --> 22:28.651
- We can get the DA
to call his PO.

22:28.695 --> 22:30.305
We can get it all
straightened out.

22:30.349 --> 22:32.176
- No, I can't risk my dad
going back to Rikers.

22:32.220 --> 22:35.310
- Daniela, Greco's the one
who sent Diego into the ocean.

22:35.354 --> 22:37.007
I went in after him.
I pulled him out.

22:37.051 --> 22:38.444
He died right in front of me.

22:38.487 --> 22:39.793
You're gonna let Greco
walk around free?

22:39.836 --> 22:42.317
- I hate Greco, too,
for what he did to me.

22:42.361 --> 22:44.450
But Diego's dead.

22:44.493 --> 22:47.714
Nothing's bringing him back.

22:47.757 --> 22:49.280
I have to protect
my father now.

22:49.324 --> 22:50.543
I'm sorry.

22:50.586 --> 22:52.109
- Diego--

22:52.153 --> 22:58.812
♪

23:00.727 --> 23:02.337
- I'm assuming you
asked us here to tell us

23:02.381 --> 23:03.947
you're dropping the charges.

23:03.991 --> 23:06.515
I understand you lost
your only witness.

23:06.559 --> 23:08.996
- Yeah, because your client
used political clout

23:09.039 --> 23:10.214
to have someone threaten her.

23:10.258 --> 23:11.651
- I have no idea
what you're talking about.

23:11.694 --> 23:14.088
- Would you like us to open
a witness tampering case?

23:14.131 --> 23:16.482
- Without the girl's
cooperation?

23:16.525 --> 23:18.919
- We're also investigating
the circumstances

23:18.962 --> 23:20.181
around Diego's death.

23:20.224 --> 23:21.748
- Hold on.
- No.

23:23.619 --> 23:27.493
I am devastated
by Diego's death.

23:27.536 --> 23:29.669
Any drowning is a tragedy.

23:29.712 --> 23:33.629
But a lifeguard, that's a
supervisor's worst nightmare.

23:33.673 --> 23:37.372
Yes, Diego and I
had our issues,

23:37.416 --> 23:39.374
but I never wanted this
to happen.

23:39.418 --> 23:41.289
- And yet it did.

23:41.332 --> 23:46.468
And a 19-year-old is dead
directly because of you.

23:46.512 --> 23:48.078
- I did not give that order.

23:48.122 --> 23:50.559
- There were two qualified
lifeguards on duty.

23:50.603 --> 23:51.821
Why don't you talk to them?

23:51.865 --> 23:53.432
- Trust me, we will.

23:53.475 --> 23:55.434
- I'm not the monster
you think I am.

23:56.913 --> 24:00.134
I've devoted my entire career
to saving lives,

24:00.177 --> 24:01.701
not destroying them.

24:01.744 --> 24:06.749
- You know, men like you
become so good at lying,

24:06.793 --> 24:11.058
they even start to believe
the ones they tell themselves.

24:11.101 --> 24:18.021
♪

24:22.635 --> 24:24.985
You cannot let this bastard
back on the job.

24:25.028 --> 24:26.769
- Yeah. I agree.

24:26.813 --> 24:28.467
But we don't have
a rape case anymore.

24:31.470 --> 24:33.689
There were two lifeguards
on duty

24:33.733 --> 24:35.256
when Diego drowned, right?

24:35.299 --> 24:37.084
- Velasco had to go in.

24:37.127 --> 24:38.825
The way Muncy tells it,

24:38.868 --> 24:42.089
Daniela admitted to not
even knowing how to swim

24:42.132 --> 24:43.917
when Greco tried to hire her.

24:43.960 --> 24:46.528
- If Greco knowingly hired
unqualified lifeguards

24:46.572 --> 24:48.269
in exchange for sex--

24:48.312 --> 24:50.184
- We may have
a manslaughter case.

24:50.227 --> 24:51.402
- The first step,
let's find out

24:51.446 --> 24:52.578
how many drownings
happened at that beach

24:52.621 --> 24:54.318
with lifeguards
Greco qualified.

24:56.582 --> 24:59.149
- They all drowned
at Jonas Bronck Beach.

24:59.193 --> 25:01.935
- All involving lifeguards
qualified by Greco,

25:01.978 --> 25:04.415
no other risk factors,
no drugs, no intoxication.

25:04.459 --> 25:05.460
- Well, what about
these lifeguards?

25:05.504 --> 25:06.983
Are any of them
willing to talk?

25:07.027 --> 25:08.158
- Not without a subpoena.

25:08.202 --> 25:09.246
- They all lawyered up

25:09.290 --> 25:10.421
'cause they're all afraid
of Greco.

25:10.465 --> 25:11.945
- What about Volpe,

25:11.988 --> 25:14.034
the one who takes the timings
for the qualifications?

25:14.077 --> 25:17.080
- You think he might have
helped fake them?

25:17.124 --> 25:18.821
- Greco is facing manslaughter.

25:18.865 --> 25:24.348
Let Volpe know that
if he's complicit, he is too.

25:27.351 --> 25:29.049
- Manslaughter.

25:29.092 --> 25:30.180
Wait, what?

25:30.224 --> 25:34.750
- Ten counts, including Diego.

25:34.794 --> 25:37.057
- You were there.
I went in after Diego.

25:37.100 --> 25:39.146
- It's not about you not
going in the water.

25:39.189 --> 25:41.801
- It's about these lifeguards

25:41.844 --> 25:44.978
and Greco fixing their scores

25:45.021 --> 25:47.458
with help from you.

25:47.502 --> 25:50.505
- Why don't you talk
to us about Pinsky?

25:50.549 --> 25:52.028
You took his initial timings,
right?

25:52.072 --> 25:53.247
- Yeah.

25:53.290 --> 25:55.336
- Greco had you
doctor his score?

25:55.379 --> 25:57.425
[tense music]

25:57.468 --> 25:58.731
- I came in to talk to you guys

25:58.774 --> 26:02.082
because I felt sick
about Diego.

26:02.125 --> 26:03.997
But maybe I need a lawyer.

26:04.040 --> 26:05.433
- That's up to you.

26:05.476 --> 26:07.174
But if you get a lawyer,
we can't help you.

26:07.217 --> 26:10.786
- And you'll sink or swim right
next to your boss in court.

26:12.353 --> 26:13.876
- Look, I only
became a lifeguard

26:13.920 --> 26:15.530
to pay my way through college
and meet chicks, all right?

26:15.574 --> 26:17.097
I'm not an accomplice
to anything.

26:17.140 --> 26:18.359
- So you're saying,
it's all Greco?

26:18.402 --> 26:19.839
- Yeah, he changed the scores.

26:19.882 --> 26:21.362
- And you went along with it?

26:21.405 --> 26:22.755
- I didn't even
notice it at first.

26:22.798 --> 26:24.365
I'd write down the scores.

26:24.408 --> 26:25.932
Then when I put them
in the system,

26:25.975 --> 26:29.675
I saw that they changed by
a few seconds here and there.

26:29.718 --> 26:31.198
So I started taking
pictures on my phone.

26:31.241 --> 26:32.895
Look, it's all right here.

26:32.939 --> 26:38.205
♪

26:38.248 --> 26:40.816
- You didn't report it?

26:40.860 --> 26:42.383
- No.

26:42.426 --> 26:43.732
I like my job.

26:45.125 --> 26:47.170
- Have you heard enough?

26:47.214 --> 26:48.563
- Forget manslaughter.

26:48.607 --> 26:51.044
If Greco knowingly hired
incompetent lifeguards

26:51.087 --> 26:53.350
in exchange for sex and money
and then those lifeguards

26:53.394 --> 26:54.961
failed to save
drowning victims,

26:55.004 --> 26:57.572
that is depraved indifference
to human life.

26:57.616 --> 26:59.487
That's murder two.

26:59.530 --> 27:01.620
- Take him down.

27:06.973 --> 27:07.190
.

27:07.234 --> 27:08.888
- Can you state your
name and title, please?

27:08.931 --> 27:10.106
- Anna Callas.

27:10.150 --> 27:11.542
I'm an investigator
for the New York City

27:11.586 --> 27:12.761
Department of Health.

27:12.805 --> 27:14.589
We analyze drowning
incident reports

27:14.633 --> 27:16.504
for all public beaches.

27:16.547 --> 27:20.464
- Can you identify
these ten people?

27:20.508 --> 27:23.119
- Victims of drownings
at Jonas Bronck Beach

27:23.163 --> 27:25.252
under Chief Greco's tenure,

27:25.295 --> 27:27.558
all cases involving
a lifeguard attempt.

27:27.602 --> 27:29.560
- Lifeguard attempts
that failed?

27:29.604 --> 27:31.084
- That's correct.

27:31.127 --> 27:32.912
The ME report
showed none of them

27:32.955 --> 27:34.696
had alcohol or drugs
in their system.

27:34.740 --> 27:37.830
- Now, the lifeguards that
made the failed attempts,

27:37.873 --> 27:39.832
what did they all
have in common?

27:39.875 --> 27:41.224
- They were all qualified
and hired

27:41.268 --> 27:43.923
by County Administrator
Paul Greco.

27:43.966 --> 27:45.098
- Thank you.

27:47.666 --> 27:49.929
- The drownings
were ruled accidental?

27:49.972 --> 27:51.495
- Yes, but that's standard--

27:51.539 --> 27:53.454
- So there was no conclusion
that lifeguard incompetence

27:53.497 --> 27:54.498
was the cause?

27:54.542 --> 27:56.805
- No, that's beyond
our purview.

27:56.849 --> 27:58.589
- I see.

27:58.633 --> 27:59.590
Thank you.

28:01.767 --> 28:04.900
- I served as chief lifeguard
for the City of New York

28:04.944 --> 28:06.902
for 25 years before I retired.

28:06.946 --> 28:10.689
During that time, I evaluated
thousands of rescue cases,

28:10.732 --> 28:13.256
most of them successful.

28:13.300 --> 28:17.696
- Now, I am going to draw
your attention to some

28:17.739 --> 28:19.393
that unfortunately were not.

28:22.265 --> 28:27.444
Julio Vela, 14 years old,
drowned July 16, 2012.

28:27.488 --> 28:29.229
Lifeguard on duty
was Mariel Kemp.

28:29.272 --> 28:30.883
Now, witnesses
reported that Kemp

28:30.926 --> 28:34.060
was slow to enter the water
and then was unable to reach

28:34.103 --> 28:35.757
the victim in time.

28:35.801 --> 28:39.282
Now, in your expert opinion,
with conditions calm and flat,

28:39.326 --> 28:41.807
as they were that day,
would that ever have happened

28:41.850 --> 28:44.635
with a qualified lifeguard?

28:44.679 --> 28:47.508
- No.
- No.

28:47.551 --> 28:52.382
Alea Shihabi, age 26,
drowned August 8, 2016.

28:52.426 --> 28:54.471
Lifeguard on duty
was Dylan Marks.

28:54.515 --> 28:58.171
He was observed on his phone,
which delayed him

28:58.214 --> 29:00.564
in sounding
the submersion signal.

29:00.608 --> 29:03.263
- In my opinion,
that would not have occurred

29:03.306 --> 29:05.787
with a qualified lifeguard.

29:05.831 --> 29:10.966
- Greg Turner, age 28,
drowned July 5, 2015.

29:11.010 --> 29:12.794
Lifeguard on duty
was Sean Davis--

29:12.838 --> 29:17.625
- Who was observed
heading into the water

29:17.668 --> 29:19.670
and turning right around.

29:19.714 --> 29:22.630
[suspenseful music]

29:22.673 --> 29:28.375
♪

29:28.418 --> 29:30.290
- As head lifeguard
at Jonas Bronck Beach,

29:30.333 --> 29:33.467
I report directly
to Chief Paul Greco.

29:33.510 --> 29:35.774
I supervise all
on-duty lifeguards,

29:35.817 --> 29:37.297
distribute bay assignments,

29:37.340 --> 29:39.342
and I also administer
qualification tests.

29:39.386 --> 29:40.735
- How do you take the timings?

29:40.779 --> 29:42.519
- I use a stopwatch,
then write the results

29:42.563 --> 29:46.480
on an application form
for Chief Greco to evaluate.

29:46.523 --> 29:49.831
- How does he evaluate them?

29:49.875 --> 29:51.572
- He looks them over.

29:51.615 --> 29:56.533
But I came to realize that he
sometimes changed the scores.

29:56.577 --> 29:58.709
- And what did you do
when you realized that?

29:58.753 --> 30:00.755
- I took screenshots
of my initial timings

30:00.799 --> 30:02.235
on my cell phone.

30:02.278 --> 30:04.541
- People's exhibit three.

30:04.585 --> 30:07.588
Can you read
the initial timings

30:07.631 --> 30:10.373
for ocean qualification,
please?

30:10.417 --> 30:13.637
- Frank Pinsky, 7:42.

30:13.681 --> 30:16.858
Mariel Kemp, 7:50.

30:16.902 --> 30:19.382
Marks, 8:20. Davis, 8:35.

30:19.426 --> 30:21.907
- And since none of these four
made the required timing,

30:21.950 --> 30:23.734
how did they all
end up assigned

30:23.778 --> 30:25.127
to Jonas Bronck Beach?

30:25.171 --> 30:28.217
- Greco adjusted their scores,

30:28.261 --> 30:31.003
said he had requalified them.

30:31.046 --> 30:32.526
- Meaning what?

30:32.569 --> 30:34.136
- He had sex
with the candidates,

30:34.180 --> 30:37.009
or they kicked back
10% of their salary.

30:37.052 --> 30:38.401
He called it pay or lay.

30:38.445 --> 30:40.360
- And you know this how?

30:40.403 --> 30:42.797
- He told me when
I confronted him

30:42.841 --> 30:45.321
and recorded the conversation
on my cell.

30:45.365 --> 30:47.149
- People's exhibit four.

30:47.193 --> 30:51.240
- Hell yeah, she requalified,
on her knees. [laughs]

30:51.284 --> 30:52.894
Come on, what do you care?

30:52.938 --> 30:57.203
Come on, you want a crack
at her, too, huh?

30:57.246 --> 30:59.335
- Who is the defendant
referring to?

30:59.379 --> 31:00.902
- Mariel Kemp.

31:00.946 --> 31:04.079
Her score changed
from 7 minutes, 50 seconds

31:04.123 --> 31:06.473
to 6 minutes flat,

31:06.516 --> 31:09.737
enough to qualify to be
a lifeguard at the beach.

31:09.780 --> 31:11.391
- Nothing further.

31:13.393 --> 31:17.179
- Mr. Volpe, you knew about
the scores being changed

31:17.223 --> 31:18.615
and said nothing?

31:18.659 --> 31:19.747
- I did.

31:19.790 --> 31:21.923
And it is
with deep regret I didn't--

31:21.967 --> 31:25.622
- Did that regret start before
or after the DA's Office

31:25.666 --> 31:28.060
offered you a deal to testify?

31:28.103 --> 31:34.936
♪

31:34.980 --> 31:36.938
I thought so.

31:36.982 --> 31:38.331
Nothing further.

31:45.164 --> 31:47.166
- Hey.

31:47.209 --> 31:49.951
- Hey. You headed home?

31:49.995 --> 31:51.083
- Yeah.

31:51.126 --> 31:52.519
How's it going?

31:52.562 --> 31:55.087
- It's a lot of data
for the jury to absorb.

31:55.130 --> 31:56.740
- I think you're
getting to them.

31:56.784 --> 31:58.612
I saw tears.

31:58.655 --> 32:01.049
- Want a job
as a jury consultant?

32:01.093 --> 32:04.835
- Sure, less chance
of getting shot.

32:08.448 --> 32:10.450
- You know, you slept
like a baby last night.

32:10.493 --> 32:12.843
It's the first time in--

32:12.887 --> 32:14.976
in a while that
you didn't wake up at all.

32:15.020 --> 32:15.934
- Mm.

32:18.153 --> 32:19.415
Fin.

32:19.459 --> 32:21.896
When he retires,
maybe he should be a shrink.

32:25.769 --> 32:27.510
You gonna be late then?
- Yeah, very late.

32:27.554 --> 32:29.860
Greco testifies tomorrow.

32:29.904 --> 32:32.254
- Okay. Good night.

32:32.298 --> 32:34.691
You got this, Counselor.

32:40.915 --> 32:44.832
- Being a lifeguard takes
discipline and integrity.

32:44.875 --> 32:46.877
It's a hard job.

32:46.921 --> 32:48.792
But I'm damn proud
of the work we do.

32:48.836 --> 32:51.665
- Do you consider yourself a
man of integrity, Chief Greco?

32:51.708 --> 32:52.796
- I do.

32:52.840 --> 32:55.277
Now, have I had
sexual involvements

32:55.321 --> 32:57.323
with lifeguards underneath me?

32:57.366 --> 33:00.282
Yes, all consensual.

33:00.326 --> 33:03.024
But I have never hired someone

33:03.068 --> 33:04.983
who was unfit for the job.

33:09.770 --> 33:13.469
- You were sure that your
lifeguards could do the job.

33:13.513 --> 33:15.558
But in these ten drownings,

33:15.602 --> 33:17.169
they underperformed,
didn't they?

33:17.212 --> 33:20.868
- Even the most experienced
lifeguard can lose a swimmer.

33:20.911 --> 33:22.000
It's always a tragedy.

33:22.043 --> 33:24.002
- A tragedy?

33:24.045 --> 33:26.395
Let me ask,
do you lose sleep over it?

33:26.439 --> 33:27.744
- Objection. Relevance.

33:27.788 --> 33:29.572
- A little latitude,
please, Your Honor?

33:29.616 --> 33:32.227
- I'll allow,
but move this along.

33:32.271 --> 33:34.403
- I'm understaffed.

33:34.447 --> 33:38.668
My budget is cut,
and every year, it gets worse.

33:38.712 --> 33:40.714
I got drunks on the beach,

33:40.757 --> 33:42.803
people letting their kids
wander around,

33:42.846 --> 33:45.023
people with no business
getting in the water.

33:45.066 --> 33:46.459
And you know what happens?

33:46.502 --> 33:48.504
Then we need to get in,
we need to risk our lives.

33:48.548 --> 33:52.378
- Yeah, but that is
your job, isn't it?

33:52.421 --> 33:56.469
- Oh, look at you,
your suit and tie.

33:56.512 --> 33:58.949
You have no idea what it's like

33:58.993 --> 34:02.214
to have people's lives
in your hands, do you?

34:02.257 --> 34:08.611
♪

34:08.655 --> 34:10.265
Well, people don't think
about it like this.

34:10.309 --> 34:14.878
The ocean is a wilderness.

34:14.922 --> 34:18.665
And men like me
are the breakwater,

34:18.708 --> 34:21.798
the only single barrier

34:21.842 --> 34:23.800
between a fun day at the beach

34:23.844 --> 34:26.412
and some out-of-shape
stupid person becoming

34:26.455 --> 34:28.109
a part of the food chain.

34:28.153 --> 34:31.286
And rarely--rarely do those
life-or-death moments

34:31.330 --> 34:32.940
come down
to a matter of seconds.

34:32.983 --> 34:37.118
Most of the time, it's IQ
points and common sense.

34:37.162 --> 34:39.381
- Is that why you sent
Diego Rodriguez

34:39.425 --> 34:40.817
into the water that day?

34:40.861 --> 34:43.385
Because you thought
he lacked common sense?

34:43.429 --> 34:44.386
- Objection.

34:44.430 --> 34:46.301
- Sustained.

34:46.345 --> 34:49.130
- Diego was a drunk

34:49.174 --> 34:50.740
who showed up hungover,

34:50.784 --> 34:53.178
and I can't have that
on my beach.

34:53.221 --> 34:55.876
- And so you gave the order
to send him out

34:55.919 --> 34:57.965
to swim laps to and from a buoy

34:58.008 --> 35:00.489
a quarter mile out
in a rip current?

35:00.533 --> 35:01.708
- Your Honor!

35:01.751 --> 35:03.536
- You're damn right
I gave that order.

35:06.582 --> 35:07.975
But I didn't know
there'd be a rip

35:08.018 --> 35:10.064
any more than I wanted
that kid dead.

35:14.808 --> 35:19.465
But that beach and the lives
on it are my responsibility.

35:19.508 --> 35:22.555
All mine.

35:22.598 --> 35:24.513
It's my ass on the line.

35:26.080 --> 35:28.561
I'm the boss,

35:28.604 --> 35:30.954
and all my lifeguards know it.

35:30.998 --> 35:37.918
♪

35:58.199 --> 35:58.330
.

35:58.373 --> 36:01.202
- So Pinsky was on the beach
when Diego drowned.

36:01.246 --> 36:03.161
- Yeah, he dipped his toe in.

36:03.204 --> 36:04.814
It's hard to say
what he was scared of more,

36:04.858 --> 36:06.381
the riptide or Greco.

36:08.688 --> 36:09.863
- Find out.

36:19.525 --> 36:20.961
- What's up, Frank?

36:24.051 --> 36:25.618
- My lawyer says
I shouldn't talk to you.

36:25.661 --> 36:28.011
- Well, you're not a suspect.

36:28.055 --> 36:29.839
Let me ask,

36:29.883 --> 36:31.928
why have you been
coming to court?

36:34.192 --> 36:37.064
- Show support for Chief Greco.

36:39.153 --> 36:41.547
He made it clear
we all needed to show up.

36:44.724 --> 36:49.990
I--I didn't know Diego
was gonna go under.

36:50.033 --> 36:50.991
I thought he'd be okay.

36:51.034 --> 36:53.428
He was a strong swimmer.

36:53.472 --> 36:55.213
- And you're not.

36:55.256 --> 36:57.127
- I'm all right, but...

36:59.260 --> 37:01.262
That's not why I didn't go in.

37:05.527 --> 37:09.836
Greco told me not to,
no matter what.

37:09.879 --> 37:11.272
- You listened.

37:11.316 --> 37:14.797
[suspenseful music]

37:14.841 --> 37:16.321
- I should have gone in.

37:22.457 --> 37:24.590
- What does Greco
have on you, Frank?

37:30.552 --> 37:34.252
Whatever it is,
it's not on you.

37:38.125 --> 37:40.432
You know what he did
to other guys.

37:48.614 --> 37:51.225
- He's got pictures

37:51.269 --> 37:55.751
of me and him and a couple
of the other guys doing...

37:55.795 --> 37:57.100
stuff.

37:59.189 --> 38:00.800
And he sent them to me,
and he said that

38:00.843 --> 38:02.410
if I didn't do what he said,
he was gonna show them

38:02.454 --> 38:06.545
to everybody, you know, my--
my family, my--my girlfriend.

38:11.376 --> 38:14.509
He's right,
what he said in there.

38:14.553 --> 38:16.946
He's the boss.

38:16.990 --> 38:18.470
He's got all the power.

38:21.603 --> 38:23.823
- So take it back.

38:23.866 --> 38:31.004
♪

38:32.397 --> 38:35.661
- That coward Pinsky is lying.

38:35.704 --> 38:38.011
- When I put him on the stand,
the jury will have to decide.

38:38.054 --> 38:39.665
- Hold up.
Let's slow this down.

38:39.708 --> 38:41.493
- What am I paying you for?

38:41.536 --> 38:44.147
- To tell you when to shut up
and accept you've lost.

38:44.191 --> 38:45.410
- Where's all that
common sense you were

38:45.453 --> 38:47.020
bragging about having, huh?

38:47.063 --> 38:49.109
- Jury's never
gonna convict.

38:49.152 --> 38:50.328
If they do, I'll just appeal.

38:50.371 --> 38:52.895
- No, no, no. It's over, Greco.

38:52.939 --> 38:56.334
The political clout
you bought, that has limits.

38:56.377 --> 39:00.381
Pinsky's got the photos
you used to blackmail him.

39:00.425 --> 39:03.471
Now, I'm giving you a chance
to serve out your time

39:03.515 --> 39:05.865
without everybody knowing
the truth about you.

39:05.908 --> 39:07.257
- Oh, yeah?

39:07.301 --> 39:09.172
[tense music]

39:09.216 --> 39:10.826
What's that?

39:10.870 --> 39:15.744
- That you are a manipulative,
little big man,

39:15.788 --> 39:20.401
with a fiefdom built on sand,
and it's all coming down.

39:25.188 --> 39:26.276
- What are you offering?

39:26.320 --> 39:32.587
♪

39:32.631 --> 39:34.154
- Thank you, Carisi.

39:34.197 --> 39:35.721
Yeah.

39:35.764 --> 39:40.726
Greco will plead
to ten counts of manslaughter.

39:40.769 --> 39:42.380
- Served consecutively,

39:42.423 --> 39:44.338
he'll be in prison
till he's 70.

39:44.382 --> 39:48.037
- Yeah, good work, both of you.

39:48.081 --> 39:49.387
- We'll tell Martina.

39:52.302 --> 39:55.349
- There's a memorial
for Diego at the beach.

39:55.393 --> 39:58.178
- Yeah.
I'll send my condolences.

40:02.138 --> 40:03.270
Velasco.

40:07.709 --> 40:13.323
You lost someone, and it's easy
to take that personally.

40:13.367 --> 40:18.720
So you feel sorry,
but not for yourself.

40:18.764 --> 40:20.940
You did everything right.

40:20.983 --> 40:24.247
[somber music]

40:24.291 --> 40:27.250
- Thank you.

40:27.294 --> 40:28.817
- Mean it.

40:28.861 --> 40:35.781
♪

40:54.800 --> 40:57.759
[dramatic music]

40:57.803 --> 41:04.723
♪

41:24.743 --> 41:27.659
[wolf howls]
